      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Additional titles of interest:</p>
        <p>AN ISLAND CHRISTMAS. By Lynn Joseph. Illustrated by Catherine Stock. Clarion. $14.95. (Ages 5 to 9) Rosie describes the rituals of her family's Christmas celebration in Trinidad. There are sorrel flowers to be gathered for a sweet drink, and currants for the cake. There's music in the streets, a tree, soursop ice cream, presents and church. She gets a steel drum. Delightful.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Additional titles of interest:</p>
        <p>AN ISLAND CHRISTMAS. By Lynn Joseph. Illustrated by Catherine Stock. Clarion. $14.95. (Ages 5 to 9) Rosie describes the rituals of her family's Christmas celebration in Trinidad. There are sorrel flowers to be gathered for a sweet drink, and currants for the cake. There's music in the streets, a tree, soursop ice cream, presents and church. She gets a steel drum. Delightful.</p>
        <p>THE SNOW SPEAKS. By Nancy White Carlstrom. Illustrated by Jane Dyer. Little, Brown. $14.95. (Ages 4 to 8) Two children celebrate the first snow of the season, sure of the magic it brings. Charming illustrations.</p>
        <p>THANK YOU, SANTA. By Margaret Wild. Illustrated by Kerry Argent. Scholastic. $12.95. (Ages 5 to 9) Bedridden with a post-Christmas cold, Samantha writes a thank-you note to Santa. They correspond -- she writing from Australia, he from the North Pole.</p>
        <p>CHILDREN'S BOOKS</p>
